com.clearent.idtech.android.family

Interface ApplicationContext

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ApplicationContextFor3In1Reader

    public interface ApplicationContext
    This interface describes what is needed for the DeviceFactory to successfully create an object that can be used to control a '2 in 1' reader (insert, or swipe).

      • getIdTechXmlConfigurationFileLocation

        String getIdTechXmlConfigurationFileLocation()
        Clearent will attempt to call its servers to check for peripheral specifications for the android device you are using. If the configuration is not found you can provide an alternate configuration based on IDTech's format. This is optional. Only provide if you want to use this as a backup used with the device_configurePeripheralAndConnect method.

      • disableAutoConfiguration

        boolean disableAutoConfiguration()
        By default the Clearent framework will configure the reader based on an emv certification process Clearent went through. To disable this feature set the auto configuration to false. Do not disable unless you've been notified previously by the framework (isReady in the listener was called successfully) that a configuration was applied successfully. 126-2.0.0 By default the framework will no longer perform configuration. This will be removed in a future release.
